# AWS S3 Fundamentals

## What S3 Is

Amazon Simple Storage Service (S3) is an object storage service that allows you to store and retrieve any amount of data from anywhere.

## Why S3 Matters

S3 is essential for cloud storage, backups, and static content hosting. Understanding permissions and policies is key for security and access control.

---

# Core Concepts

## Buckets

- Containers for objects (files)
- Must have globally unique names
- Can be public or private

## Objects

- Files stored in S3
- Each has a key (name), metadata, and version (if versioning enabled)

## Permissions

- IAM policies control who can access S3 buckets/objects
- Bucket policies allow fine-grained access control
- ACLs provide legacy object-level permissions

